## 1. Automated Run Deviation & Corrective Action Log

Automated Liquid Handler (Library Prep) | Volumetric pipetting error flagged mid-plate; inconsistent reagent distribution in columns 4–6. | Air bubble detection triggered due to suboptimal reagent viscosity at cold storage temperature. | Paused run. Manually primed the dispensing lines. Adjusted system settings to implement a 2-second pre-aspiration delay for high-viscosity master mixes to ensure precise delivery. |
High-Throughput Sequencer (NGS Run) | Drop in cluster density metrics accompanied by an elevated %Phasing rate early in the sequencing run. | Inaccurate library quantification during the pooling stage due to fluorometer calibration drift. | Aborted the sub-standard run. Recalibrated the Qubit fluorometer using fresh standards. Re-quantified the library pool, adjusted dilution calculations, and successfully re-loaded the flow cell. |
Droplet Digital PCR (ddPCR / qPCR) | Total droplet count dropped below the strict quality control threshold (<10,000 droplets per well). | Suboptimal emulsion generation caused by a microscopic partial blockage within the microfluidic cartridge channels. | Rejected the affected wells. Cleaned the generator housing block, replaced the disposable cartridge components, and verified droplet consistency via an oil-blank test run. |

